1 C. Except as otherwise provided in this act, if, contrary to
2 the rental agreement or Section 118 of this title, the landlord
3 willfully or negligently fails to supply heat, running water, hot
4 water, electric, gas or other essential service, the tenant may give
5 written notice to the landlord specifying the breach and thereafter
6 may:
7 1. Upon written notice, immediately terminate the rental
8 agreement; or
9 2. Procure reasonable amounts of heat, hot water, running
10 water, electric, gas or other essential service during the period of
11 the landlord's noncompliance and deduct their actual and reasonable
12 cost from the rent; or
13 3. Recover damages based upon the diminution of the fair rental
14 value of the dwelling unit landlord's noncompliance, at the
15 discretion of the court, including reasonable attorney fees; or
16 4. Upon written notice, procure reasonable substitute housing
17 during the period of the landlord's noncompliance, in which case the
18 tenant is excused from paying rent for the period of the landlord's
19 noncompliance.
20 D. Except as otherwise provided in this act, if there is a
21 noncompliance by the landlord with the terms of the rental agreement
22 or Section 118 of this title, which noncompliance renders the
23 dwelling unit uninhabitable or poses an imminent threat to the
24 health and safety of any occupant of the dwelling unit and which
Req. No. 13042 Page 5
1 nonc ompliance is not remedied as promptly as conditions require, the
2 tenant may immediately terminate the rental agreement upon written
3 notice to the landlord which notice specifies the noncompliance.
4 E. If an action for possession or recovery of rent is brought
5 under Sections 131 or 132 of this title, and the matter is found in
6 favor of the tenant or if the landlord is determined to have brought
7 the action in bad faith, the tenant may recover reasonable attorney
8 fees and damages equivalent to two (2) months rent.
9 F. All rights of the tenant under this section do not arise
10 until he or she has given written notice to the landlord or if the
11 condition complained of was caused by the deliberate or negligent
12 act or omission of the tenant, a member of his or her family, his or
13 her animal or pet or other person or animal on the premises with his
14 or her consent.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
